<DocsLayout title="Screenshots - ThinkPad - Docs" sidebar={sidebar} toc={toc} issuesUrl="https://github.com/ether-strannik/PrismChart/issues">
	<style>
		h1 {
			font-size: 1.8rem;
			font-weight: 600;
			margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
		}

		.tagline {
			color: #666;
			margin-bottom: 2rem;
		}

		h2 {
			font-size: 1.2rem;
			font-weight: 600;
			margin: 2rem 0 1rem;
			padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
			border-bottom: 1px solid #e5e5e5;
		}

		h2:first-of-type {
			margin-top: 0;
		}

		p {
			color: #333;
			margin-bottom: 1rem;
		}

		.section-intro {
			font-weight: 500;
			color: #000;
			margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
		}

		img {
			max-width: 100%;
			border-radius: 6px;
			margin: 1rem 0 1.5rem;
		}

		.note {
			color: #666;
			font-size: 0.95rem;
			padding: 1rem;
			background: #f5f5f5;
			border-radius: 4px;
			margin: 1.5rem 0;
		}
	</style>

	<h1>Screenshots</h1>
	<p class="tagline">Capture, organize, and review your chart images.</p>

	<img src="/docs/prismchart/thinkpad/ThinkPad-20260126-5.jpg" alt="ThinkPad Screenshots" />

	<h2 id="taking-screenshots">Taking Screenshots</h2>
	<p class="section-intro">Capture key moments during trading.</p>

	<p>Use the Presentation Dialog in PrismChart to take screenshots at important points - entries, exits, key levels hit. Screenshots save to the PrismChart/Screenshots folder where ThinkPad automatically detects them.</p>

	<h2 id="assigning-to-trades">Assigning to Trades</h2>
	<p class="section-intro">Link screenshots to specific positions.</p>

	<p>Switch the mode dropdown from Notes to Screenshots. The file tree shows an Unassigned folder with your screenshots listed by date and time.</p>

	<p>Right-click a screenshot and select Assign to Position. The Trades Manager opens - select the matching position. Enter a sequence number when prompted (1 for first screenshot, 2 for second, and so on).</p>

	<p>All assigned screenshots appear under their position in the tree, numbered in sequence.</p>

	<h2 id="viewing-screenshots">Viewing Screenshots</h2>
	<p class="section-intro">Browse your trade documentation.</p>

	<p>Click any screenshot under a position to open the large viewer on the right. Use the zoom controls and navigation buttons to move between images. Click and drag to pan around zoomed images.</p>

	<h2 id="reordering">Reordering</h2>
	<p class="section-intro">Fix the sequence after assignment.</p>

	<p>Right-click any screenshot under a position and select Reorder. The dialog shows all screenshots for that position - drag them into the correct order and click Apply. Files are automatically renamed to reflect the new sequence.</p>

	<h2 id="renaming">Renaming</h2>
	<p class="section-intro">Add descriptive names instead of timestamps.</p>

	<p>Right-click a screenshot and select Rename. Enter a descriptive name like "Breakout entry" - the symbol is preserved while the date/time is replaced with your custom name.</p>

	<p class="note">Rename key screenshots you reference often or when creating presentation-ready sequences.</p>
</DocsLayout>
